                    Whole-School Approach Evidence
                  </Typography>
                  <Typography variant="body" className="mb-4">
                    Research consistently demonstrates that whole-school approaches to mental health and wellbeing are more effective than isolated interventions. A systematic review by Weare and Nind (2011) found that multi-component, whole-school approaches that include changes to the school environment, curriculum teaching, and partnerships with families and communities have the strongest evidence of effectiveness.
                  </Typography>
                  <Typography variant="body">
